The paper discusses experimental characterization and analytical modeling of error sources in 3D NAND flash memory, and proposes techniques to mitigate these errors. This work involves circuit-level and structural changes in memory technology, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of computer architecture (cs.AR), embedded systems (cs.ET), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses error correction techniques, which are studied in the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
